      "text": "Design autocomplete/ type ahead search",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Design autocomplete/ type ahead search",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PA5DLmmk2wVlJXHNpJVvQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 54.3739013671875,
      "y": 100.56015014648438,
      "width": 760.6195068359375,
      "height": 1300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b93",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 892935986,
      "version": 889,
      "versionNonce": 839451570,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782565328437,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Questions :\n\nq. Autocomplete like google?\nyes\n\nq. scale\n1 billion rpd\n\nq. imp features?\nWhen a word is typed, top n suggestions are given\n\nq. engligh only? or unicode chars\nunicode\n\nq. spelling mistakes\nyes\n\nq. how to identify frequency? using previous search results?\nyes\n\n\nFunctional requirements:\n1. When a seq of chars are typed, we want to return top n searches starting \nwith that chars\n\nNFR\nScalable\nAvailable : 99.9 SLA\nDurability : 6 9s\nlow latency\n\nBack of envelope calc:\n\nTraffic\n\n1b searches a day\n\nReads\n10^9 / 100000 = 10000 rps\n\nOptimise for reads\n\nStorage:\n1b * 3 words * 5 chars * 1 byte\n= 15b * 10^9\n= 15kb * 10^6\n= 15GB daily\nover a year 10% new queries\n15gb + ( 0.1 * 365 * 15gb ) =\n15 + 365 * 1.5gb = 15 + 545 = 560 gb over a year\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Questions :\n\nq. Autocomplete like google?\nyes\n\nq. scale\n1 billion rpd\n\nq. imp features?\nWhen a word is typed, top n suggestions are given\n\nq. engligh only? or unicode chars\nunicode\n\nq. spelling mistakes\nyes\n\nq. how to identify frequency? using previous search results?\nyes\n\n\nFunctional requirements:\n1. When a seq of chars are typed, we want to return top n searches starting \nwith that chars\n\nNFR\nScalable\nAvailable : 99.9 SLA\nDurability : 6 9s\nlow latency\n\nBack of envelope calc:\n\nTraffic\n\n1b searches a day\n\nReads\n10^9 / 100000 = 10000 rps\n\nOptimise for reads\n\nStorage:\n1b * 3 words * 5 chars * 1 byte\n= 15b * 10^9\n= 15kb * 10^6\n= 15GB daily\nover a year 10% new queries\n15gb + ( 0.1 * 365 * 15gb ) =\n15 + 365 * 1.5gb = 15 + 545 = 560 gb over a year\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
